BRIEFING:
.AVIATION... BREEZY TO LOCALLY STRONG TRADE WINDS WILL PERSIST OVER THE NEXT SEVERAL DAYS. REMNANT MOISTURE FROM A FRONTAL BOUNDARY WILL SAG SOUTHWARD OVER THE ISLANDS LATE TONIGHT INTO SUNDAY. THIS FEATURE SHOULD HELP GENERATE SCATTERED TO NUMEROUS SHOWERS ALONG MAINLY WINDWARD LOCATIONS WITH PERIODS OF ASSOCIATED MVFR CEILINGS AND VISIBILITY. OTHERWISE, VFR CONDITIONS SHOULD GENERALLY PREVAIL FOR LEEWARD LOCATIONS.
AIRMET SIERRA WILL LIKELY BE NEEDED FOR KAUAI LATER TONIGHT TO ACCOUNT FOR LOW CEILINGS AND REDUCED VISIBILITY AS THE BAND OF MOISTURE BEGINS TO PUSH OVER THE ISLANDS.
AIRMET TANGO REMAINS IN EFFECT FOR MODERATE LOW-LEVEL TURBULENCE OVER AND DOWNWIND OF ISLAND TERRAIN. THIS AIRMET WILL LIKELY CONTINUE OVER THE NEXT SEVERAL DAYS.
